27/05/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Visiting EU foreign policy chief Catherine Ashton and Interior Minister Ivica Dacic signed an agreement Thursday (May 26th) on security procedures in the exchange and protection of classified information. The document allows the Serbian Army and police to participate in EU peacekeeping missions. "This agreement represents a further sign of Serbia approaching the precondition for the EU and EU security policy," Dacic said. (Tanjug, Xinhua, Emportal - 26/05/11)
